{
  "texts": [
    "The main contributions of this paper are summarized as following:",
    "(1) Construction of the RoParQ Benchmark: We present a novel dataset enriched with highquality paraphrases generated by proprietary models to rigorously test cross-paraphrase consistency.",
    "(2) Proposal of the XParaCon Metric: We introduce a robust evaluation metric that provides a precise and intuitive measure of a model's semantic invariance.",
    "(3) Efficacy of Paraphrase-Aware Alignment: We demonstrate that our reasoning-based SFT method effectively mitigates inconsistency, showing that explicitly training models on paraphrase invariance enables lightweight models to achieve robust performance comparable to that of larger models.",
    "Given the set of questions q i ∈ Q in the dataset, we denote each question as q original."
  ]
}